<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - FLYWHEEL HOUSING AND FLYWHEEL INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FLYWHEEL HOUSING AND FLYWHEEL INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flywheel housing as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install a new square cut O-Ring to seal the camshaft and a new flywheel housing
                        gasket over the locating dowels. Use grease to hold the gasket in place (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150780">7.80</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the flywheel housing on the crankcase locating dowels and tighten the
                        mounting bolts to the specified torque. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150781">7.81</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check flywheel housing bore concentricity and face runout. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="ef4150716">7.16</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">
                        <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="ef4150715">7.15</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    which appear earlier in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rear seal and wear sleeve. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="e415_134.xml" xrefid="hl4150702">"Rear Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve Installation"
                    </hotlnk>
                    procedure which appears earlier in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flywheel and ring gear assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150703.xml" xrefid="hl4150703">"Flywheel Reconditioning"</hotlnk>, in this
                    section, for the installation procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_E41508.xml" xrefid="e41508">TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150780" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12195" filename="../figcg1/CG12195.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.80. Install Flywheel Housing Gasket and Camshaft O-Ring.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150781" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12196" filename="../figcg1/CG12196.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.81. Tighten Flywheel Housing Bolts.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">On engines with S/N 691360 and Below.</emph>Remove the gasket material which
                    overhangs the edge of the front cover (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_158.xml" xrefid="ef4150782">7.82</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and the flywheel housing
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_158.xml" xrefid="ef4150783">7.83</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ), at the oil pan rail.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
